				<h2 class="pt-10"><b class="font-serif italic">Cleopatra</b>, the last of the Pharaohs</h2>
				<p>
					We know from Plutarch that during Octavian's fifth consulship, which he shared with Antony, Octavian defeated Cleopatra and Antony in Egypt.<button
						popovertarget="pop06">6</button
					> This was <i>before</i> he was given the title Augustus, which is clear as he was still known simply as (Imperator) Caesar.
				</p>

				<div
					class="text-red-800 float-right m-5 hidden w-1/2 text-balance p-3 text-center font-sans text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider md:block dark:text-amber-200"
				>
					Ancient chronology is linked to ours by direct or indirect synchronisms with Roman dates.
				</div>

				<!--
